{{Infobox scientist | name = David Berson | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | nationality = American | fields = [[Neuroscience]] | workplaces = [[Brown University]] | alma_mater = [[Brown University]], [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] | doctoral_advisor = | doctoral_students = | known_for = [[Intrinsically photosensitive retinal ganglion cells]] | awards = }}
'''David M. Berson''' is [[Professor]] of [[Medical Science]] at [[Brown University]]. He helped lead the way in the discovery of a third class of [[mammal]]ian [[Photoreceptor cell|photoreceptors]] by providing the first [[electrophysiological]] recordings from intrinsically photosensitive [[retina]]l [[ganglion]] cells.<ref>{{cite web|title = Berson, David |url = https://vivo.brown.edu/display/dberson |publisher = [[Brown University]]}}</ref>
