'''Eva Jacqueline Longoria Bastón'''<ref name=telly>{{cite news |author=<!-- No by-line. --> |title=Eva Longoria Files for Divorce from Tony Parker |date=November 18, 2010 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/8142106/Eva-Longoria-files-for-divorce-from-Tony-Parker.html |access-date=May 23, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151211035509/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/8142106/Eva-Longoria-files-for-divorce-from-Tony-Parker.html |archive-date=December 11, 2015 |dead-url=no}}</ref>{{r|Longoria Twitter (July 26, 2016)|Bacardi (2016)}} (born March 15, 1975)<ref>{{Cite news|last=Hale |first=Clinton |title=High and Lows of TEVA |newspaper=[[San Antonio Express-News]] |location=San Antonio |date=June 27, 2007}}</ref> is an American actress, producer, director, activist and businesswoman. After a series of guest roles on several television series, Longoria was first recognized for her portrayal of [[Isabella Braña]] on the [[CBS]] daytime soap opera ''[[The Young and the Restless]]'', on which she starred from 2001 to 2003. She is perhaps best known for her role as [[Gabrielle Solis]] on the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] television series ''[[Desperate Housewives]]'', which ran from 2004 to 2012 and for which she received [[Golden Globe Award|Golden Globe]] and [[Screen Actors Guild Award]] nominations. She has also appeared in ''[[The Sentinel (2006 film)|The Sentinel]]'' (2006), ''[[Over Her Dead Body]]'' (2008), ''[[Cristiada (film)|For Greater Glory]]'' (2012), ''[[Frontera (2014 film)|Frontera]]'' (2014), ''[[Lowriders (film)|Lowriders]]'' (2016) and ''[[Overboard (2018 film)|Overboard]]'' (2018). From 2015 to 2016, Longoria starred as Ana Sofia Calderón on the short-lived [[NBC]] sitcom ''[[Telenovela (TV series)|Telenovela]]'', and served as an executive producer for the [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] television series ''[[Devious Maids]]''. She has also been involved with social issue documentaries as an Executive Producer including ''[[Food Chains (film)|Food Chains]]'' and ''[[The Harvest (2010 film)|The Harvest]]''.

Longoria has also appeared in several [[advertising campaign]]s and has been named one of Hollywood's most beautiful women by several publications, including ''[[People en Español]]'' and ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazines. She currently holds modeling contracts with [[L'Oréal]], [[Hanes]], and [[New York & Company|New York & Co]], among others.

==Early life and education==
Longoria was born in [[Corpus Christi, Texas]],<ref name="Jr.2010">{{cite book|author=Henry Louis Gates Jr.|title=Faces of America: How 12 Extraordinary People Discovered their Pasts |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=meYbj1E6Ki8C&pg=PA234|date=1 September 2010|publisher=NYU Press|isbn=978-0-8147-3265-6|pages=234}}</ref> the youngest of four daughters born to [[Mexican-American]] ([[Tejano]]) parents, Ella Eva (Mireles) and Enrique Longoria, Jr.<ref name=telly/><ref>The Late Show with Stephen Colbert, February 16, 2016. "I'm ninth generation American. ... My family lived under five different flags without ever moving. We didn't cross the border, the border crossed us."</ref><ref>[http://www.rumorficial.com/hollywood/eva-longoria-latest-interview-in-latina-magazine/ ''Latina Magazine'' Interview], "Longoria says 'even with my real traditional Mexican grandma' "</ref><ref>[http://latina.com/fashion/celebrity/exclusive-eva-longoria-parkers-got-down-home-style Latina.com] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090524051625/http://latina.com/fashion/celebrity/exclusive-eva-longoria-parkers-got-down-home-style |date=May 24, 2009 }} "Longoria says 'I'm Mexican'."</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Wick|first=Krista|title=Eva Longoria Rallies for Barack at DNC |url=http://www.etonline.com/news/124779_Eva_Longoria_Speaks_at_Democratic_National_Convention/index.html|work=[[Entertainment Tonight]]|accessdate=May 24, 2013|date=September 6, 2012}}</ref> One of her sisters had special needs, as she told [[Redbook]] in 2016:<blockquote>“There was never any resentment, because I saw how hard my mother worked and all she did for my sister [with special needs], and I wanted to do whatever I could to help. We all did.”<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://people.com/food/eva-longoria-wendys-burger-recipe-rachael-ray/|title=Eva Longoria Spills All the Burger Secrets She Learned from Working at Wendy's|work=PEOPLE.com|access-date=2018-07-30|language=en}}</ref></blockquote>She was raised [[Roman Catholic]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.independent.ie/entertainment/news-gossip/eva-longoria-unbelievable-1366738.html|title=Eva Longoria: Unbelievable |work=[[Irish Independent|Independent]]|date=May 4, 2008|accessdate=May 23, 2010|first=Barry|last=Egan}}</ref> She did not speak Spanish growing up, not learning the language until 2009.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/127997-can-eva-longoria-speak-spanish-her-telenovela-character-may-hit-home-for-many|title=Eva Longoria Can Relate To Her 'Telenovela' Part|last=Gallagher|first=Caitlin|work=Bustle|access-date=2018-06-02|language=en}}</ref>  While in high school, she worked at a [[Wendy's]] restaurant part-time for three years to earn for her [[Quinceañera]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Eva Longoria returns to work at Corpus Christi Wendy's |url=http://www.chron.com/entertainment/article/Eva-Longoria-returns-to-work-at-Corpus-Christi-1756024.php |work=[[Houston Chronicle]] |accessdate=May 24, 2013|date=May 27, 2008}}</ref><ref name=":0" /> Longoria previously told the press how her years in fast food as a teen shaped her work ethic.<blockquote>“I couldn’t wait to get to work and make my own money,”</blockquote>Longoria earned her Bachelor of Science degree in [[kinesiology]] at [[Texas A&M University-Kingsville]].<ref name="Riggs2006">{{cite book|author=Thomas Riggs|title=Contemporary Theatre, Film and Television|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wuVkAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=January 21, 2012|date=February 3, 2006|publisher=Gale / Cengage Learning|isbn=978-0-7876-9040-3}}</ref><ref name="degrees">{{cite web |title=Eva Longoria Graduates With a Master's Degree in Chicano Studies |url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/eva-longoria-graduates-with-a-masters-degree-in-chicano-studies-2013225 |work=[[Us Weekly]] |date=2013-05-22 |author=Galla, Brittany |accessdate=2015-09-17}}</ref> During this time, she won the title of Miss Corpus Christi USA in 1998. After completing college, Longoria entered a talent contest that led her to Los Angeles; shortly after, she was spotted and signed by a [[talent agent|theatrical agent]].<ref name="DH">{{cite web|url=http://www.darkhorizons.com/features/678/eva-longoria-for-the-sentinel |title=Exclusive Interview: Eva Longoria for "The Sentinel"|last=Fischer|first=Paul |date=April 11, 2006|publisher=darkhorizons.com|accessdate=June 13, 2008}}</ref> While auditioning for roles, Longoria worked as a headhunter for four years.<ref>{{cite web|title=Eva Longoria: Hardly Desperate as Actress, Producer and Restaurateur|url=http://www.success.com/articles/984-eva-longoria-hardly-desperate-as-actress-producer-and-restaurateur |work=[[SUCCESS (magazine)|Success]]|accessdate=May 24, 2013}}</ref>

She received her master's degree in [[Chicano Studies]] from [[California State University, Northridge]], in May 2013 following three years of study. Her [[thesis]] was entitled, "Success STEMS From Diversity: The Value of [[Latinas]] in [[STEM fields|STEM Careers]]."<ref name=degrees/><ref>{{cite web|title=Eva Longoria graduates with master's degree in Chicano studies |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2013/may/23/entertainment/la-et-mg-eva-longoria-graduates-masters-chicano-studies-20130523 |work=Los Angeles Times|date=May 23, 2013|accessdate=November 10, 2013|first=Nardine|last=Saad}}</ref>

==Career==
Longoria landed her first television role in 1999 after meeting Executive Producer Gary Ghiaey at a political reception in Los Angeles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hiphopsince1987.com/2014/women/eva-longoria-covers-maxims-issue-year-photo/|title=Eva Longoria cover's Maxim's first issue of the new year|first=Quinelle|last=Holder|publisher=Hip-Hop Since 1987|date=2014-01-07|accessdate=2018-05-28}}</ref> Longoria guest-starred in an episode of ''[[Beverly Hills, 90210]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?pp_cat=18&art_id=16974&sid=7568898&con_type=1 |title=Desperate housewife with politics in mind |first=Bob |last=Tourtellotte |work=The Standard |date=April 21, 2006 |accessdate=July 16, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016022137/http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?pp_cat=18&art_id=16974&sid=7568898&con_type=1 |archivedate=October 16, 2012 |df= }}</ref> Another guest appearance in ''[[General Hospital]]'' the same year brought her big break on the [[CBS Daytime]] soap opera ''[[The Young and the Restless]]'', portraying [[Isabella Braña]] from 2001 to 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.people.com/people/eva_longoria |title=Eva Longoria|work=People |year=2011 |accessdate=July 16, 2011}}</ref>
After leaving ''The Young and the Restless'', Longoria appeared in the [[Dick Wolf]] revival of ''[[Dragnet (series)#Remakes|Dragnet]]''. Following ''Dragnet'', she starred in ''[[Señorita Justice]]'', a poorly received [[direct-to-video]] film, and a television film titled ''The Dead Will Tell''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Before They Were Stars: Eva Longoria|url=http://horror.about.com/od/horroractorsandactresses/ig/Before-They-Were-Stars/EvaLongoriaDead.htm|work=About.com |accessdate=September 22, 2012}}</ref>

[[File:Eva Longoria Cannes.jpg|upright|thumb|left|Longoria in 2006 at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] premiere of ''[[Pan's Labyrinth]]'']]

In 2003, Longoria was cast as [[Gabrielle Solis]] in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] comedy-drama ''[[Desperate Housewives]]'', later commenting on her career success by stating, "I think it's funny when people say I'm an overnight sensation, because I've been working at it for 10 years."<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jessica |last=Hundley |title=4 Eva |date=September 2006 |work=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |url=http://www.maximonline.com/articles/index.aspx?a_id=7282 |accessdate=January 23, 2007 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930163635/http://www.maximonline.com/articles/index.aspx?a_id=7282 |archivedate=September 30, 2007}}</ref>
Shortly after her debut on ''Desperate Housewives'', Longoria starred in a direct-to-video film titled ''Carlita's Secret'', for which she was also co-producer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latinpost.com/articles/2641/20131003/eva-longoria-tv-show-vega-v-latina-actress-newest-television.htm|first=Nicole|last=Thompson|title=Eva Longoria TV Show: 'Vega v. Vega' is Latina Actress' Newest Television Production|publisher=Latin Post|date=2013-10-03|accessdate=2018-05-28}}</ref>

In 2006, she was nominated for a [[Golden Globe Award]] for Best Performance by an Actress in a Television Series – Musical or Comedy along with her co-stars in ''Desperate Housewives.''<ref>{{cite web|title=2006 Golden Globe Nominees and Winners|url=http://tvdramas.about.com/od/tvshowsaz/a/goldglobe2006.htm|work=About.com|accessdate=September 22, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110113042635/http://tvdramas.about.com/od/tvshowsaz/a/goldglobe2006.htm|archivedate=January 13, 2011|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Longoria was awarded the [[ALMA Award]] and named entertainer of the year that year. She also starred opposite [[Michael Douglas]] and [[Kiefer Sutherland]] in the 2006 thriller ''[[The Sentinel (2006 film)|The Sentinel]]'', which was her first major role in a theatrical feature movie. In 2006, she played the character Sylvia in ''[[Harsh Times]]'', starring [[Freddy Rodríguez (actor)|Freddy Rodríguez]] and [[Christian Bale]].<ref>{{cite web |title=About Eva Longoria |url=https://movies.yahoo.com/person/eva-longoria-parker/biography.html |work=Yahoo movies |accessdate=September 22, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026173224/http://movies.yahoo.com/person/eva-longoria-parker/biography.html |archivedate=October 26, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>

In the 2000s, Longoria appeared in several high-profile [[advertising campaign]]s and numerous [[List of men's magazines|men's magazines]], reaching No. 14 in the [[FHM]] "Sexiest Women 2008" poll. She was featured on the cover of various international women's magazines, including ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'', ''[[Marie Claire]]'' and ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]''.<ref>[http://www.fhm.com/100sexiest/EvaLongoria Eva Longoria | 100 Sexiest 2008] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080428103352/http://www.fhm.com/100sexiest/EvaLongoria |date=April 28, 2008 }}. FHM.com. Retrieved on September 18, 2011.</ref> ''[[People en Español]]'' listed her among its "Most Beautiful People" for 2003.<ref>{{cite web|title=People en Español – 25 Most Beautiful 2003|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9g4aY0WoEJQ |publisher=YouTube|accessdate=September 22, 2012}}</ref> Longoria continues to be included in lists of Hollywood's Most Beautiful. She was listed as No. 1 in ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]''<nowiki/>'s Hottest Female Stars of 2005 and 2006, becoming the first woman to top the list in two consecutive years.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://today.msnbc.msn.com/id/12799889/ns/today-entertainment/t/longoria-repeats-atop-maxims-hot|title=Longoria repeats atop Maxim's Hot 100|agency=Associated Press|work=[[MSNBC]]|date=May 15, 2006|accessdate=April 14, 2012}}</ref> She was ranked No. 9 in the magazine's Hot 100 of 2007 list.<ref>[http://www.maximonline.com/Girls/Evalongoria/slideshow/1133/47.aspx? #9 Eva Longoria in the Hot 100 of 2007] "Maxim Magazine, 2007"</ref> In honor of Maxim's 100th issue in 2006, Longoria was featured on a {{convert|75|by|110|ft|adj=on}} vinyl mesh replica of its January 2005 cover located in a [[Clark County, Nevada]] desert.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2006-04-05-longoria-maxim_x.htm|title=Longoria: Plus-sized cover girl|last=Keck|first=William |date=April 5, 2006|work=USA Today|accessdate=June 13, 2008}}</ref> More recently, she was ranked No. 14 of [[People (magazine)|''People'']]'s Most Beautiful 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=PEOPLE's Most Beautiful 2011|url=http://www.people.com/people/package/gallery/0,,20360857_20481337,00.html#20936744|date=April 13, 2011|work=People|accessdate=August 9, 2011}}</ref> ''People'' named her one of 2012 Most Beautiful at Every Age.<ref>{{cite web|title=2012 Most Beautiful at Every Age – Eva Longoria|url=http://www.people.com/people/package/gallery/0,,20360857_20360861,00.html#21144155|work=People|accessdate=April 25, 2012|author=Karen J. Quan |date=April 20, 2012}}</ref>

[[File:Eva Longoria Cannes white dress.jpg|thumb|right|Longoria at the [[2010 Cannes Film Festival]]]]

In January 2007, Longoria was chosen to be the first face of [[Bebe Stores|Bebe Sport]].<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.just-style.com/news/actress-eva-longoria-named-as-face-of-bebe-sport_id96062.aspx |title=Eva Longoria named as face of Bebe Sport |work=just-style.com |year=2011 |accessdate=July 16, 2011}}</ref> She appeared in the Spring/Summer 2007 campaign, photographed by Greg Kadel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bebe.com/010407-Eva-Longoria-First-Face-BEBE-SPORT-News-History-Investor-info-NONCOMMERCE-hidden-nodes-Specia/b/318520011 |title=Eva Longoria – the First Face of BEBE SPORT! |publisher=Bebe.com |date=January 4, 2007 |accessdate=April 14, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090723090913/http://www.bebe.com/010407-Eva-Longoria-First-Face-BEBE-SPORT-News-History-Investor-info-NONCOMMERCE-hidden-nodes-Specia/b/318520011 |archivedate=July 23, 2009 |df= }}</ref> The actress also holds contracts with [[L'Oréal]], [[Hanes]], and New York & Co.<ref>[http://www.enjoyfashion.com/fashion/fashion-news/actress-eva-longoria-to-be-a-new-face-of-bebe-sport-20070105-32.html Actress Eva Longoria to be a new face of Bebe Sport] EnjoyFashion, January 15, 2007</ref> Longoria also contracts with [[Magnum (ice cream)|Magnum Ice-Cream]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mad.co.uk/BreakingNews/BreakingNews/Articles/20cd42cdcf5d4a1a8b4a30105ca88c35/Unilever-sales-to-exceed-expectations.html |title=Unilever sales to exceed expectations|last=Varley |first=Melinda |date=May 8, 2008 |publisher=mad.co.uk|accessdate=June 13, 2008}}</ref> and [[Heineken International|Heineken]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Eva-becomes-new-face-of-Dutch-beer/articleshow/4763574.cms |work=The Times of India |title=Eva becomes new face of Dutch beer |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100405012055/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Entertainment/Eva-becomes-new-face-of-Dutch-beer/articleshow/4763574.cms |archivedate=April 5, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/news/2005/4/5/loreal_paris_signs_eva_longoria_as.htm |title=L'Oréal Paris Signs Eva Longoria as New Spokesperson |publisher=hispanicbusiness.com |accessdate=June 13, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224071025/http://www.hispanicbusiness.com/news/2005/4/5/loreal_paris_signs_eva_longoria_as.htm |archivedate=December 24, 2008 |df= }}</ref> She was a part of Microsoft's "I'm A PC" ad campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://imapc.lifewithoutwalls.com/?u=Eva&icid=realpc |title=I'm A PC |publisher=microsoft.com |accessdate=October 26, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081220131751/http://imapc.lifewithoutwalls.com/?u=Eva&icid=realpc |archivedate=December 20, 2008 |df= }}</ref> She and Tony Parker have appeared together in campaigns for [[London Fog (company)|London Fog]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://sanantonio.bizjournals.com/sanantonio/stories/2009/10/19/daily19.html | first=San | last=Antonio | title=Tony and Eva Longoria Parker chosen for fashion campaign | date=October 21, 2009}}</ref> Longoria became a spokesperson for L'Oréal Paris in 2005 and was still being featured in L'Oréal TV commercials and print ads {{as of|2016|lc=y}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://morungexpress.com/aishwarya-eva-longoria-look-charismatic-in-new-loreal-paris-campaign/|title=Aishwarya, Eva Longoria look charismatic in new L’Oreal Paris campaign |publisher=The Morung Express|date=2016-01-20|accessdate=2018-05-28}}</ref> In the summer of 2010 Longoria served as a judge on ''[[The Next Food Network Star]].''<ref name="my"/> In October, Longoria hosted the [[2010 MTV Europe Music Awards|MTV Europe Music Awards 2010]] in Madrid, Spain.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2010/10/08/3032883.htm |title=Eva Longoria to host MTV Europe awards |publisher=Australian Broadcasting Corporation |accessdate=November 7, 2010|date=October 8, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2010/nov/07/lady-gaga-mtv-european-music |title=Lady Gaga triumphs at MTV European Music Awards|work=The Guardian |accessdate=November 7, 2010|author= Jason Deans|date= November 7, 2010 |location=London}}</ref>

Based on her earnings from June 1, 2009 to June 1, 2010, Longoria was ranked No. 4 on ''[[Forbes]]'' ''Prime Time's 10 Top-Earning Women'' with an estimated $12 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2010/09/17/television-top-earning-women-business-television-top-earning-women_slide_5.html|title=In Pictures: Prime Time's 10 Top-Earning Women|work=Forbes |year=2010 |accessdate=April 17, 2011|first=Lacey|last=Rose}}</ref> Longoria topped the ''Forbes'' magazine's list of the highest-paid TV actresses for 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiavision.com/news/article/entertainment/233964/eva-longoria-marcia-cross-top-forbes-list-of-highestpaid-tv-actresses/|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130103075304/http://www.indiavision.com/news/article/entertainment/233964/eva-longoria-marcia-cross-top-forbes-list-of-highestpaid-tv-actresses/|dead-url=yes|archive-date=January 3, 2013|title=Eva Longoria, Marcia Cross top Forbes' list of highest-paid TV actresses|date=September 29, 2011|publisher=Indiavision news}}</ref>

In 2013, Longoria professed that she is a "cat lady" and appeared as a spokesperson for [[Sheba]] cat food.<ref>{{cite web |last=Terrero |first=Nina |title=Eva Longoria Admits She's a Cat Lady |url=http://nbclatino.com/2013/03/08/video-eva-longoria-admits-shes-a-cat-lady/ |date=March 8, 2013 |website=NBC Latino |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130411112022/http://nbclatino.com/2013/03/08/video-eva-longoria-admits-shes-a-cat-lady/ |archive-date=April 11, 2013 |dead-url=no}}</ref>

From 2013, she served as one of the executive producers of ''[[Devious Maids]]'' and directed the season two premiere, "An Ideal Husband". In 2016, she also starred in the fourth season, in the episode "Once More Unto the Bleach". She is also an executive producer of the documentaries ''[[The Harvest (2010 film)|The Harvest]]'' and ''[[Food Chains]],'' for which she won a [[James Beard Foundation Award]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jamesbeard.org/blog/2015-book-broadcast-and-journalism-awards-complete-winner-recap|title=The 2015 Book, Broadcast, and Journalism Awards: Complete Winner Recap|website=www.jamesbeard.org|language=en|access-date=2018-02-05}}</ref>

In 2015, [[NBC]] announced plans for a [[sitcom]] called ''[[Telenovela (TV series)|Telenovela]]'' in which Longoria starred as a popular [[telenovela]] actress. It was filmed with a [[Single-camera setup|single camera]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://naples.floridaweekly.com/news/2015-02-12/Arts_%28and%29_Entertainment_News/Tyler_Perry_show_features_dynamic_characters.html|title=Celebrity Extra|last=Elavsky|first=Cindy|publisher=[[King Features]]|date=February 12, 2015|accessdate=February 18, 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150220235442/http://naples.floridaweekly.com/news/2015-02-12/Arts_%28and%29_Entertainment_News/Tyler_Perry_show_features_dynamic_characters.html|archivedate=February 20, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It ran for only one season.

In 2017, Longoria directed the season three finale episode of the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] comedy ''[[Black-ish]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2017/tv/news/eva-longoria-empire-charlotte-frost-1202399673/|title=Eva Longoria on Her ‘Empire’ Role, Directing and Possible ‘Desperate Housewives’ Reunion|first=Elizabeth|last=Wagmeister|work=Variety|date=2017-04-26|accessdate=2018-05-28}}</ref>

In 2018, Longoria attended the premiere for her new film, "Dog Days" with co-stars [[Vanessa Hudgens]] (Tara) and [[Nina Dobrev]] (Elizabeth) on August 5, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.feelingthevibe.com/news/vanessa-hudgens-nina-dobrev-most-adorable-dogs-at-dog-days-premiere-photos-inside/|title=Vanessa Hudgens, Nina Dobrev, & Most Adorable Dogs at 'Dog Days' Premiere - Photos Inside {{!}} Feeling the Vibe Magazine|website=blog.feelingthevibe.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-09}}</ref>

==Other ventures==
[[File:EvaLongoriaApr2011.jpg|thumb|left|Longoria at a book signing for her book ''Eva's Kitchen: Cooking with Love for Family and Friends'' in April 2011]]

In March 2008, Longoria opened the restaurant [[BlueZoo|Beso]] (which means "kiss" in Spanish) in Hollywood, along with partner and [[celebrity chef]] [[Todd English]]. The restaurant is located on [[Hollywood Boulevard]] and is accompanied by Kiss, a Victorian-themed [[nightclub]] on the floor above.<ref name="vegasnews">[http://www.vegasnews.com/16354/eva-longoria-parker-to-dazzle-the-strip-with-grand-opening-of-beso-and-eve-at-citycenter.html "Eva Longoria Parker to Dazzle The Strip"], ''Vegas News'', December 1, 2009</ref> The Hollywood Beso was scheduled to be the focus of a pilot episode for a tentative [[reality show|reality series]] called ''Beso: Waiting on Fame'', to air on [[VH1]] in late 2010.<ref>{{Cite news|author=Tanklefsky, David |title=VH1 To Produce Record 44 Original Shows In 2010 |url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/article/451665-VH1_To_Produce_Record_44_Original_Shows_In_2010.php |work=Broadcasting Cable |date=April 19, 2010}}</ref>
In 2009, Longoria and various investor-partners opened a Beso restaurant, with a nightclub called Eve above it, in the [[The Crystals (Las Vegas)|Crystals]] retail and entertainment district of [[CityCenter]] in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]].<ref name="vegasnews" />

In 2011, the corporation Beso LLC, owner of the Vegas restaurant-and-nightclub venture, with listed assets of about $2.5 million and Longoria as a 32 percent shareholder, filed for [[Chapter 11, Title 11, United States Code|Chapter 11]] protection, entering bankruptcy proceedings, in order to restructure nearly $5.7 million in debt and other liabilities.<ref>[http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/2011/jan/06/eva-longorias-beso-files-bankruptcy-restructure-de/ "Eva Longoria's Beso files bankruptcy to restructure debt"] ''Las Vegas Sun'', January 6, 2011</ref> On July 28, 2011, the U.S. [[Bankruptcy in the United States|Bankruptcy Court for Nevada]] ordered Longoria to appear in Las Vegas on August 20 in order to be examined about the bankrupt restaurant's finances.<ref>[http://www.vegasinc.com/news/2011/jul/28/langoria-ordered-appear-court-over-beso/ "Longoria to be quizzed by Las Vegas restaurant investors"] ''Vegas Inc'', July 28, 2011</ref>

Her first book, ''Eva's Kitchen: Cooking with Love for Family and Friends'', was published in April 2011.<ref name="my">{{cite web|url=http://www.mysanantonio.com/default/article/Eva-Longoria-dishes-on-her-first-cookbook-guilty-1317216.php|title=Eva Longoria dishes on her first cookbook, guilty pleasure and more|last=Quintanilla|first=Michael|publisher=My San Antonio|accessdate=April 6, 2011}}</ref> In terms of food-related promotions, in 2012 and 2013, Longoria paired with [[Iron Chef]] [[Michael Symon]] for a promotion for [[PepsiCo]]'s [[Lay's|Lay's potato chips]] contest called "Do Us A Flavor". The promotion encourages consumers to submit new flavor ideas and fans to vote for their favorite on [[Facebook]]. The person who creates the winning flavor is awarded $1 million or one percent of chip flavor's net sales.<ref>{{cite web|title=Lay's Potato Chips Teams Up With Eva Longoria And Iron Chef Michael Symon|url=http://www.pepsico.com/pressrelease/lays-potato-chips-teams-up-with-eva-longoria-and-iron-chef-michael-symon-to-invi07202012.html |accessdate=April 6, 2013}}</ref>

In 2015, Longoria announced that she had teamed up with [[sportswear (fashion)|sportsware]] manufacturer Sunrise Brands to create a women's apparel collection, set to launch Fall 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Eva Longoria Turns Her Passion Into a Business|url=http://wwd.com/fashion-news/designer-luxury/eva-longoria-sunrise-sporttswear-10177049/|publisher=WWD|author=Jane Palmieri |date=July 8, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sunrisebrands.com/brands/eva-longoria/|title=Eva Longoria /// Sunrise Brands|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.licensemag.com/license-global/eva-longoria-creates-fashion-label |publisher=Licensemag.com|date=July 17, 2015|title=Eva Longoria Creates Fashion Label}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/eva-longoria-launch-clothing-line-807462 |title=Eva Longoria to Launch Clothing Line |last=Reed |first=Sam |website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=July 8, 2015}}</ref>

In March 2017, Eva Longoria launched her clothing line website on her official site.

==Philanthropy==
[[File:Eva Longoria Parker and Victoria Beckham.jpg|upright|thumb|right|250px|Longoria with [[Victoria Beckham]] in 2010]]

In 2006 Longoria founded Eva's Heroes, a charity which helps developmentally disabled children.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100205034534/http://www.evasheroes.org/about_bod.asp Board of Directors] Eva's Heroes</ref> She is the national spokesperson for PADRES Contra El Cancer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.iamhope.org/press/releases/060809gala.php |title=PADRES Contra el Cáncer National Spokesperson Eva Longoria Hosts event Set |date=September 6, 2006 |accessdate=June 13, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080611145907/http://www.iamhope.org/press/releases/060809gala.php |archivedate=June 11, 2008 |df= }}</ref> She signed shoes for the Spirit of Women Red Shoe Celebrity Auction.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/eva-longoria-joins-other-celebrities-for-online-red-shoe-charity-auction-to-benefit-womens-heart-health-58121682.html|title=Eva Longoria Joins Other Celebrities for Online Red Shoe Charity Auction to Benefit Women's Heart Health|work=[[PR Newswire]]}}</ref> Longoria also supports the Clothes Off Our Back Foundation, [[OmniPeace]], the [[National Center for Missing and Exploited Children]], the National Stroke Association, [[Project HOME]] and [[St. Jude Children's Research Hospital]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/celebrity/64-eva-longoria|title=Eva Longoria's Charity Work|publisher=looktothestars.org}}</ref> Longoria is an executive producer of [[Shine Global]] Inc.'s documentary ''[[The Harvest (documentary)|The Harvest]]'' which is focused on the 500,000 child migrant farm workers in the U.S. and promote awareness and support to enact the [[Children's Act for Responsible Employment (CARE Act)]].<ref name="Shine Global Inc.">{{cite web | url=http://www.shineglobal.org/?page_id=19 | title=The Harvest/La Cosecha, The Story of the Children Who Feed America | publisher=Shine Global | year=2010 | accessdate=2011-05-27 |archivedate=2011-01-04|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110104234610/http://www.shineglobal.org/index.php/hero-of-the-week/harvest/}}</ref><ref name=LRA>{{cite web |url=http://roybal-allard.house.gov/News/DocumentSingle.aspx?DocumentID=206669 |title=Congresswoman Lucille Roybal-Allard, Press Release |date=September 15, 2010 |publisher=Offices of Congresswoman Lucille Roybal-Allard |accessdate=May 27, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pL_WWSnU0Yg | title=Eva Longoria interviewed by Anderson Cooper on October 20, 2009}}</ref>

Her other charity, the Eva Longoria Foundation aims to close the education gap plaguing Latinas<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marieclaire.com/culture/news/a10513/eva-longoria-evas-heros-changing-the-world/|title=Eva Longoria Is Empowering the Latina Community Through Education|accessdate=February 27, 2016}}</ref> and confront Latino poverty.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hispanicexecutive.com/2013/eva-longoria-foundation/|title=Leave it to Eva|accessdate=February 27, 2016}}</ref> She has stated that, "The Eva Longoria Foundation supports programs which help Latinas excel in school and attend college. Additionally, we work to provide Latina entrepreneurs with career training, mentorship, capital and opportunity."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latina.com/celebrity/eva-longoria-projects-causes#6|title=The Ultimate Advocate: Eva Longoria's Projects & Causes|accessdate=February 27, 2016}}</ref> The foundation offers nine-week "parent engagement" courses to help Latino parents and has a mentorship program for Latinas and other extracurricular activities<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/2016/09/10/eva-longoria-knows-no-limits/89949228/|title=Eva Longoria knows no limits|work=USA TODAY Hispanic Living magazine|author=Laura Castañeda}}</ref> as well as loans to help Latina-owned businesses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marieclaire.com/career-advice/interviews/a16425/eva-longoria-advice-latinas/|title=Eva Longoria and Nina Garcia Have a Candid Chat About What It Means to Be Latina Today}}</ref> It is co-funded by philanthropist [[Howard Graham Buffett|Howard Buffett]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.1843magazine.com/features/the-political-passion-of-eva-longoria/|title=The Political Passion Of Eva Longoria|work=The Economist 1843|date= May 3, 2016}}</ref> son of investor [[Warren Buffett]].

Longoria was named Philanthropist of the Year in 2009 by ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' for 'her commitment to Latino causes and giving back to the community.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/thr-honors-eva-longoria-parker-91332 |title=THR honors Eva Longoria Parker |work=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=February 6, 2014| date=November 16, 2009}}</ref> She appeared on [[Fort Boyard (TV series)|''Fort Boyard'']] in 2009, helping attract more than €20,000 for the [[Make-A-Wish Foundation]].<ref>{{cite episode|title=Eva Longoria|series=Fort Boyard (French version)|network=[[France 2]]|airdate=June 27, 2009|season=20|number=1|minutes=115}}</ref>

In 2009, Longoria enrolled in a Master's program in [[Chicano Studies]] and [[political science]] at [[Cal State University, Northridge]]. According to Longoria, "because of my involvement with the [[National Council of La Raza|NCLR]] and my charity work, I really wanted a better, more authentic understanding of what my community has gone through so I can help create change."<ref>{{cite web| first = Mariela| last = Rosario| title = Eva Longoria Parker is at the Head of the Class| work = [[Latina (magazine)|Latina]]| date = September 17, 2009| accessdate = September 19, 2009| url = http://www.latina.com/entertainment/celebrity/eva-longoria-parker-head-class}}</ref> She graduated with a master's degree in Chicano Studies in May 2013.<ref>{{cite web| first = Rebecca| last = Macatee| title = Eva Longoria Graduates With Master's Degree—See Her Cap-and-Gown Pics!| work = E! News| date = May 23, 2013| accessdate = May 23, 2013| url = http://ca.eonline.com/news/422183/eva-longoria-graduates-with-master-s-degree-see-her-cap-and-gown-pics}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Gala|first=Brittany|title=Eva Longoria Graduates With a Master's Degree in Chicano Studies|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/eva-longoria-graduates-with-a-masters-degree-in-chicano-studies-2013225|work=[[Us Weekly]]|accessdate=May 24, 2013|date=May 22, 2013}}</ref>

In September 2009 Longoria was appointed to a bi-partisan commission called to determine establishing a [[National Museum of the American Latino]].<ref>[http://www.thomas.gov/cgi-bin/bdquery/z?d110:h.r.00512: 110th Congress (2007–2008) H.R.512]. Thomas.gov. Retrieved on September 18, 2011.</ref>
In October 2012 Longoria spoke at the [https://web.archive.org/web/20121128213615/http://www.thevarguy.com/tag/focus12/ McAfee Focus 2012] event, where the "theme of safety—beyond computers—emerged. Safety involving financial security, emotional security, and the other results from Longoria's philanthropic efforts."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thevarguy.com/var-guy/eva-longoria-and-var-guy-rumors-are-false|title=Eva Longoria and The VAR Guy: The Rumors Are False|first1=Oct|last1=23|first2=2012 The VAR Guy &#124; The VAR|last2=Guy}}</ref>

In March 2017, Longoria was listed by UK-based company Richtopia at number 42 in the list of 200 Most Influential Philanthropists and Social Entrepreneurs Worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://richtopia.com/inspirational-people/top-200-philanthropists-social-entrepreneurs|title=Philanthropists & Social Entrepreneurs Top 200: From Elon Musk to Melinda Gates, These Are the Most Influential Do-Gooders in the World|work=Richtopia|accessdate=31 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2017/03/31/elumelu-ranked-among-top-200-global-philanthropists-social-entrepreneurs/|title=Top 200 Global Philanthropists, Social Entrepreneurs|work=ThisDayLive|accessdate=2 April 2017}}</ref>

===Politics and activism===
Longoria has a keen interest in [[Immigration to the United States|immigration]]. She accompanied a [[Mexico–United States border|border]] [[United States Border Patrol|patrol]] in Arizona and has immersed herself in the issues to understand the Mexican and the U.S. points of view.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vision.ae/views/eva_longoria|title=Eva Longoria|publisher=|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151009112007/http://vision.ae/views/eva_longoria|archivedate=October 9, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref> She has described Arizona's [[SB 1070]] immigration law as [[unconstitutional]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Celebrity politics: Eva Longoria and immigration |url=http://politicsoutdoors.com/2011/05/17/celebrity-politics-eva-longoria-and-immigration/ |date=May 17, 2011 |accessdate=February 26, 2012 |author=Meyer, David S. |work=Politics Outdoors}}</ref>

In 2012, Longoria was one of seven Californians named to the post of co-chair of [[Barack Obama]]'s [[United States presidential election, 2012|reelection]] campaign.<ref>{{cite web | title=Obama taps Villaraigosa, Longoria, others to co-chair campaign |url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2012/02/obama-taps-villaraigosa-longoria-others-to-co-chair-campaign.html |date=February 22, 2012 |accessdate=February 25, 2012 |work=Los Angeles Times |author=Hoeffel, John}}</ref> On September 6, she spoke at the [[2012 Democratic National Convention]] where she endorsed President Obama's reelection.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.c-span.org/DNC/Events/Eva-Longoria-at-the-2012-Democratic-National-Convention/C3797183/|title=Eva Longoria at the 2012 Democratic National Convention|publisher=c-span.org|accessdate=December 15, 2012}}</ref> In May 2014, she initiated the Latino Victory Project to raise funds for candidates and efforts to get out the vote.<ref>{{cite web |title=Eva Longoria Launches New Project to Boost Latino Candidates and Voting Power |date=May 5, 2015 |website=[[Fox News Latino]] |url=http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/politics/2014/05/05/eva-longoria-launches-new-project-to-boost-latino-candidates-and-voting-power/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160516175504/http://latino.foxnews.com/latino/politics/2014/05/05/eva-longoria-launches-new-project-to-boost-latino-candidates-and-voting-power/ |archive-date=May 16, 2016 |dead-url=no}}</ref> An executive producer of the documentaries ''[[The Harvest (2010 film)|The Harvest]]'' and ''[[Food Chains]]'', she is a supporter of the [[Coalition of Immokalee Workers]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Eva Longoria – Coalition of Immokalee Workers|url=http://ciw-online.org/blog/tag/eva-longoria/|website=ciw-online.org}}</ref>

Longoria spoke at the [[2016 Democratic National Convention]] in [[Philadelphia]] on July 26, 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Richardson |first=Bradford |title=Lena Dunham to Speak at Democratic National Convention |date=July 21, 2016 |work=[[The Washington Times]] |url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2016/jul/21/lena-dunham-speak-democratic-national-convention/ |accessdate=July 23, 2016}}</ref>

==Personal life==

===Relationships===
Longoria was married to actor [[Tyler Christopher (actor)|Tyler Christopher]], star of ''[[General Hospital]]'', from 2002 to 2004.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/eva_longoria/biography|title=Eva Longoria Biography|work=People|accessdate=June 13, 2008}}</ref>

[[File:Eva Longoria and Tony Parker.jpg|thumb|left|Longoria with then-husband [[Tony Parker]] at the 2008 [[Emmy Awards]]]]

Longoria met [[Tony Parker]], [[San Antonio Spurs|Spurs]] [[point guard]], in November 2004. On November 30, 2006, the couple became engaged.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,1564335,00.html|title=Eva Longoria & Tony Parker Engaged|last=Alexander|first=Bryan|date=November 30, 2006|work=People|accessdate=June 13, 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080527213640/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,26334,1564335,00.html|archivedate=May 27, 2008|df=mdy-all}}</ref> They married in a civil service on July 6, 2007, at a Paris city hall. They had a Catholic wedding ceremony at the [[Saint-Germain l'Auxerrois]] Church in Paris on July 7, 2007.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/life/people/2007-07-07-longoria-wedding_N.htm Eva Longoria, Tony Parker Make It Official, Again], ''USA Today'', July 7, 2007</ref>

On November 17, 2010, Longoria filed for divorce from Parker in Los Angeles, citing "irreconcilable differences".<ref name=abcnews>Marikar, Sheila.[http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/eva-longoria-files-divorce-tony-parker/story?id=12172329 "Eva Longoria Files for Divorce From Tony Parker"], ABCNews.com, November 17, 2010. [https://www.webcitation.org/5uJZGk331?url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/eva-longoria-files-divorce-tony-parker/story?id=12172329 WebCitation archive]</ref> In the divorce petition, Longoria requested that her maiden name be restored. She also sought [[spousal support]] from Parker.<ref name="peopledivorce">[http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20442746,00.html "Eva Longoria Files for Divorce from Tony Parker"], ''People'', November 17, 2010.</ref> The couple had a [[prenuptial agreement]] that was signed in June 2007, a month before their wedding, and amended two years later in June 2009.<ref name="edivorce">[http://ca.eonline.com/uberblog/b211768_eva_longoria_parker_files.html "Eva Longoria Parker Files for Divorce—for Real This Time"], EOnline, November 17, 2010.</ref>

Longoria told her friend [[Mario Lopez]] she had discovered hundreds of text messages from another woman on her husband's phone.<ref name="extra">[http://extratv.warnerbros.com/2010/11/eva_longoria_talks_to_mario_about_split_with_tony_parker.php "Eva Longoria's First Words on Her Divorce"], Extra, November 17, 2010.</ref> ''Extra'' identified the other woman as Erin Barry, the then-wife of [[Brent Barry]], Parker's former teammate, and revealed that the Barrys also were in the process of divorcing.<ref name="extra2">[http://extratv.warnerbros.com/2010/11/eva_longoria_tony_parker_divorce_erin_barry_brent_barry.php#ixzz15bI2M9Ba Woman Allegedly Involved in Longoria-Parker Split is Also Divorcing], Extra, November 17, 2010.</ref> In light of the divorce, Longoria cancelled her scheduled appearance at the 2010 [[American Music Awards]].{{r|extra}}

On November 19, 2010, Parker filed for divorce from Longoria in [[Bexar County, Texas]],<ref name="tmz">[http://www.tmz.com/2010/11/19/tony-parker-eva-longoria-divorce-petition-bexar-county-san-antonio-fight-jurisdiction-prenup/ "Tony Parker Files for Divorce In Texas"], TMZ, November 19, 2010</ref> on the grounds of "discord or conflict of personalities", thus establishing a legal battle over where the divorce case would be heard. Unlike Longoria's divorce petition, Parker's did not mention a prenuptial agreement and claimed that the parties would "enter into an agreement for the division of their estate".<ref name="extra3">[http://ca.eonline.com/uberblog/b212390_tony_parker_texas_two-steps_divorce.html "Tony Parker Texas Two-Steps to Divorce Court"], Extra, November 19, 2010</ref> The divorce was finalized in Texas on January 28, 2011, the same day Longoria's lawyer filed papers to dismiss her Los Angeles petition.<ref>[http://www.tmz.com/2011/01/31/evan-longoria-tony-parker-divorce-prenup-texas-california-final-desperate-housewives-san-antonio-spurs/ Eva Longoria, Tony Parker Divorced in TX], TMZ, December 31, 2011. Retrieved December 31, 2011</ref>

On December 13, 2015, Longoria reported her engagement to Mexican businessman José Antonio "Pepe" Bastón Patiño,<ref>{{cite news|title=José Bastón Patiño: Los 300|url=https://lideresmexicanos.com/300/jose-baston-patino-los-300/|accessdate=May 9, 2018|work=Líderes Mexicanos|language=es-MX}}</ref> then the president of [[Televisa]], the largest media company in Latin America.<ref>{{cite news|title=José Antonio Bastón Patiño: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=337555&privcapId=337507|accessdate=May 9, 2018|work=Bloomberg.com|date=May 9, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Clark|first1=Cindy|title=Eva Longoria is engaged|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/2015/12/13/eva-longoria-engaged/77247746/|website=USA TODAY}}</ref>  Bastón and Longoria met on a blind date arranged by a mutual friend in Mexico City; at the time, Bastón did not know who Longoria was and originally declined the invitation to meet her because of his busy schedule.<ref>{{cite news|title=Interview with Conan O'Brien|work=[[Conan (talk show)|Conan]]|date=May 8, 2018}}</ref> The couple were married in Mexico on May 21, 2016.<ref>{{cite magazine |title=Eva Longoria and José Antonio Bastón Are Married! |date=May 21, 2016 |magazine=[[People (magazine)|People]] |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,21008096,00.html |access-date=May 21, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Gomez|first1=Patrick |title=5 Things to Know About Eva Longoria's New Husband José 'Pepe' Bastón|url=http://people.com/celebrity/5-things-to-know-about-eva-longorias-husband-jose-baston/|accessdate=May 9, 2018|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=May 21, 2016|language=en}}</ref>

On December 19, 2017, it was reported that Longoria was pregnant with her first child.<ref>{{cite web|title=Eva Longoria Preggers|url=http://people.com/tv/eva-longoria-engaged-her-love-story-with-jose-pepe-baston/|website=People.com}}</ref> She gave birth to her son, Santiago, on June 19, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Eva Longoria Is a Mom! Actress Welcomes First Child, a Son, with Husband Jose 'Pepe' Baston |url=https://people.com/babies/eva-longoria-welcomes-son-santiago-enrique/ |website=PEOPLE.com}}</ref>

===Ancestry===
[[File:Eva Longoria Cannes 2.jpg|thumb|Longoria at the [[2009 Cannes Film Festival]]]]

According to research done in 2010 by [[Harvard]] professor and  ''[[Faces of America (PBS series)|Faces of America]]'' host [[Henry Louis Gates|Henry Louis Gates, Jr.]], Longoria's oldest identifiable Spanish immigrant ancestor is her ninth great-grandfather, Lorenzo Suárez de Longoria (b. [[Oviedo]], 1592), who immigrated to the [[Viceroyalty of New Spain]] (modern-day Mexico) in 1603. His family was based in a small village called Llongoria, [[Belmonte de Miranda|Belmonte de Miranda, Asturias]], Spain. [[Longoria]] is the Castellanized form of this Asturian-language surname.

In 1767, her seventh great-grandfather received almost {{convert|4000|acre|km2}} of land along the [[Rio Grande]] in a land grant from King [[Charles III of Spain]]. The family retained this land for more than a century. After the US-Mexican border was moved southwards in the aftermath of the [[Mexican–American War]], the land ended up on the American side of the border. Her family had to deal with the influx of United States settlers following the [[Mexican–American War]] and the [[American Civil War]].<ref>[https://www.pbs.org/wnet/facesofamerica/profiles/eva-longoria/8/ "Faces of America: Eva Longoria"], PBS, ''[[Faces of America]]'' series, with Professor [[Henry Louis Gates|Henry Louis Gates, Jr.]], 2010.</ref>

According to [[DNA test]]ing, Longoria's overall genetic ancestry is 70% European, 27% Asian and [[Indigenous American|Indigenous]], and 3% [[Black people|African]].<ref name="LM">{{cite web|url=http://www.latina.com/entertainment/celebrity/faces-america-reveals-eva-longoria-parkers-surprising-roots|title="Faces of America" Reveals Eva Longoria Parker's Surprising Roots |last=Miller|first=Gerri|date=February 2, 2010|work=[[Latina (magazine)|Latina magazine]] |publisher= Latina Media Ventures LLC|accessdate=March 13, 2011}}</ref> After a computer compared the DNA results of Gates's dozen guests, tests showed that she is genetically related to cellist [[Yo-Yo Ma]], who is of Chinese heritage.<ref name="LM"/> Since women have two X chromosomes and no Y chromosome, Longoria did not inherit her father's [[Y-DNA]], but she did inherit her mother's [[mitochondrial DNA]] (genetic information passed from mother to child). Longoria's mtDNA belongs to the [[Haplogroup A (mtDNA)|Haplogroup A2]], making her a direct descendant of a Native American woman, a [[Maya peoples|Mayan]] from the territory of Mexico long before it was Mexico. Her ancestors include many other Mayans on both sides of her family.<ref name="Gate's book">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=meYbj1E6Ki8C&pg=PA245&lpg=PA245&dq=eva+longoria+is+mtdna+A2#v=onepage&q=eva%20longoria%20is%20mtdna%20A2 |title=Faces of America: How 12 Extraordinary People Discovered their Pasts|pages=241–247 |last=Gates|first=Henry Louis Jr.|publisher=NYU Press|date= July 6, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?ID=ENTEN20100137069&keyword=hollywood&subcatg=MOVIESWORLD |title=Eva Longoria shocked by DNA test |date=April 4, 2010 |work=NDTV Movies |publisher=NDTV Convergence Limited |accessdate=March 13, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100407224943/http://movies.ndtv.com/movie_story.aspx?ID=ENTEN20100137069&keyword=hollywood&subcatg=MOVIESWORLD |archivedate=April 7, 2010 |df= }}</ref>

Longoria identifies as a "Texican"—a Mexican-American Texan.<ref name="Gate's book"/>

