'''Henry Henderson Institute''' (HHI) is an educational establishment in [[Blantyre]], [[Malawi]],<ref name=HDN>{{cite book |chapter-url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=FuXPkCVjzasC&pg=PA191&lpg=PA191&dq=Henry+Henderson+malawi&source=bl&ots=9xnz4k4dHb&sig=q5uXYFfMb89EHpNGKaMts_2KhGA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi84Mnq39LMAhVJ_iwKHVzMAD4Q6AEIMDAE#v=onepage&q=Henry%20Henderson%20malawi&f=false |title=Historical Dictionary of Malawi |chapter=Henry Henderson Institute (HHI) |first1=Owen J. M. |last1=Kalinga |authorlink1=Owen J. M. Kalinga |first2=Cynthia A. |last2=Crosby |publisher=[[Scarecrow Press]] |edition=3rd |date=5 September 2001 |isbn=978-0810834811 |accessdate=11 May 2016}}</ref> founded in 1909.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://digitallibrary.usc.edu/cdm/ref/collection/p15799coll123/id/80180 |website=[[University of Southern California]] |title=Henry Henderson Institute, Blantyre, Malawi, ca.1926 |accessdate=12 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://digitallibrary.usc.edu/cdm/ref/collection/p15799coll123/id/80169 |website=University of Southern California |title=Pupils and staff, Henry Henderson Institute, Blantyre, Malawi, ca.1926 |accessdate=12 May 2016}}</ref> It was named in honour of [[Henry Henderson (missionary)|Henry Henderson]] (1843-91), [[Laity|lay]] [[missionary]] of the [[Church of Scotland]], who founded the Blantyre Mission.

The original foundation included a primary school, a teacher training college, a theological college, and a technical college to teach practical skills such as carpentry, bricklaying and printing. It also served as printer for the Blantyre Mission; producing religious texts, school textbooks, and government and other daily and weekly publications. Later, training in mechanical skills was added to the curriculum. In the late 1950s, a secondary school was opened.

HHI is said to have "played a most significant role in religious, educational, and political developments in Malawi".<ref name=HDN />

The Institute now lies within the grounds of [[St Michael and All Angels Church, Blantyre]].

