{{Infobox organization | name =Refresh Bolivia | status = Charity | region = [[Bolivia]] | services = Construction, healthcare, teaching | website = https://www.refreshbolivia.com/ }} '''Refresh Bolivia''' is a student-run non profit community originating from [[Harvard University]]. The organisation is dedicated to constructing a "maternal and child care oriented community health center" in [[Cochabamba]], [[Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Teams - New Venture Competition - Harvard Business School|url=http://www.hbs.edu/newventurecompetition/social-enterprise-track/Pages/teams.aspx|website=www.hbs.edu|accessdate=9 August 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809192819/http://www.hbs.edu/newventurecompetition/social-enterprise-track/Pages/teams.aspx|archivedate=10 August 2017|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=2016 Harvard FAS Global Health & Human Rights Expo Participants|url=https://harvard-csm.symplicity.com/events/students.php?mode=list&cf=2016GHHR&_so_list_sort96bd20d133fd898464068ee1d2134680=sal_fulltime_opportunities_2c0699ebb1a8ec6465f9b6e4ec7a77a1%3Aasc|website=harvard-csm.symplicity.com|accessdate=9 August 2017|language=en}}</ref> Currently, international chapters of the organization exist at the [[University of Toronto]], [[McMaster University]], and [[Queen's University]]. According to the group, it has benefited "more than 2,000 people" by "constructing [[ecological]] bathrooms; teaching health [[workshops]] to men, women and children; and conducting research on the health needs of our target communities." Each January 20 students are recruited by the community to participate in a "two week-long service project."<ref>{{cite web|title=Refresh Bolivia Community Health Worker and Toilet Implementation|url=https://www.fordblueovalnetwork.org/refresh-bolivia-community-health-worker-and-toilet-implementation|website=Ford Blue Oval Network|accessdate=9 August 2017|language=en}}</ref>
