{{Unreferenced|date=July 2007}}
'''Relationships Australia''' (RA) is an [[Australia]]n [[Non-profit organization|not-for profit organisation]] providing professional services to support [[intimate relationship|relationships]] across Australia that began in 1948 under the name of '''Marriage Guidance Council'''. Initially providing [[family therapy|counselling]] services using [[Volunteering|volunteer]]s, they now provide a range of professional relationship support services.
Relationships Australia is approved under the "Family Relationships Services Program", which is administered by the [[Government of Australia|Australian]] [[Department of Families, Community Services and Indigenous Affairs (Australia)|Department of Families, Community Services and Indigenous Affairs]] to provide services including: [[family therapy]], [[mediation]], skills training and children's [[Childrens centre|contact service]]s. They also receive funding from [[Australian states and territories]] for services including: for people with a [[gambling problem]], and their families, [[parent]]ing skills, and [[family violence]] prevention.
==External links== *[http://www.relationships.com.au Relationships Australia]
