'''School Stream''' is a [[mobile app]] owned by Australian company School Stream that enables its users to receive information about their [[school]].<ref name="The Age">{{cite web|url = http://www.theage.com.au/victoria/school-stream-app-sends-message-to-parents-20140502-zr2z7.html|title = School Stream app sends messages to parents|accessdate = 2014-10-09|year = 2014|publisher = The Age}}</ref> The app has received press coverage throughout 2013 and 2014 and is available on the [[Apple Inc.|Apple]] and [[Google]] app stores.<ref name="Daily Telegraph">{{cite web|url = http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/newslocal/news/school-stream-smartphone-app-makes-life-easier-for-parents-says-creator-melissa-bridson/story-fngr8gwi-1226896042464|title = School Stream smartphone app makes life easier for parents|accessdate = 2014-07-08|year = 2014|publisher = Daily Telegraph}}</ref><ref name="NorthernStar">{{cite web|url = http://www.northernstar.com.au/news/take-note-its-an-app/2047853/|title = App promises to do away with school notes getting lost|accessdate = 2014-07-08|year = 2014|publisher = northernstar.com.au}}</ref>
{{Infobox company |name = School Stream |logo = |type = Private |location = Byron Bay |key_people = Melissa Bridson |industry = [[Education]] |website = {{url|www.schoolstream.com.au}} }}
== History == School Stream was founded by Melissa Bridson in 2013.<ref name="Motherpedia">{{cite web|url = http://www.motherpedia.com.au/latest-columns/article/Melissa%20Bridson/6021|title = Melissa Bridson|accessdate = 2014-07-08|year = 2014|publisher = motherpedia.com.au}}</ref> The app was officially launched in late 2013<ref name="Motherpedia">{{cite web|url = http://www.motherpedia.com.au/article/blogs/67916/a-light-bulb-moment-that-could-help-all-parents|title = The lightbuld moment that could help all parents|accessdate = 2014-07-08|year = 2014|publisher = motherpedia.com.au}}</ref> and quickly gained media attention throughout the first half of 2014.<ref name="Herald Sun">{{cite web|url = http://www.heraldsun.com.au/technology/smartphones/school-stream-smartphone-app-makes-life-easier-for-parents-says-creator-melissa-bridson/story-fni0c1du-1226896042464?nk=33af714d2f0f21a674b3c1642888d938|title = School Stream smartphone app makes life easier for parents says creator|accessdate = 2014-07-08|year = 2014|publisher = Herald Sun}}</ref> The app has also been the subject of scrutiny by the Education Review at the parent-teacher app conference. As of June 2014, the app was being rolled out to more than 1200 Catholic primary school principals in a bid to help cut down the amount of administrative work involved in keeping members of the Australian Catholic Primary Principals Association up to date with school related information.<ref name="Education Review">{{cite web|url = http://apnedmedia.uberflip.com/i/328356/43|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140907143239/http://apnedmedia.uberflip.com/i/328356/43|dead-url = yes|archive-date = 2014-09-07|title = Parent Teacher app conference|accessdate = 2014-07-08|year = 2014|publisher = Education Review}}</ref>
School Stream has been tested by a number of different schools since its launch in 2013, including [[Preshil]] independent school in Kew,<ref name="Canberra Times">{{cite web|url = http://media.canberratimes.com.au/technology/tech-talk/how-school-stream-works-for-preshil-5391892.html|title = How school stream works for Preshil|accessdate = 2014-07-08|year = 2014|publisher = canberratimes.com.au}}</ref> and Thornbury Primary School<ref>http://thornburyps.vic.edu.au/</ref> in [[Thornbury, Victoria]].
== Features == School Stream is aimed at schools and parents of school age children, allowing both parties to keep better track of school news and information that is usually passed on from a school to a parent, via the child. The app enables schools to notify parents about general information, events and excursions, share newsletters, and send out digital permission slips.
Schools purchase a licence for the app which gives them access to all of its features. Parents can sign up for the app and access the information from multiple schools without the need for different logins<ref name="news.com.au">{{cite web|url = http://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/parenting/school-stream-smartphone-app-makes-life-easier-for-parents-says-creator-melissa-bridson/story-fngqim8m-1226896042464|title = school stream app makes life easier for parents says creator Melissa Bridson|accessdate = 2014-07-08|year = 2014|publisher = news.com.au}}</ref>
